  BlogPost(
    id: '13',
    title: 'Advice to Juniors',
    summary: 'Three essential tips for juniors: Be open-minded in friendships, explore diverse clubs and activities, and maintain a healthy balance between academics and fun.',
    content:
        '1. Be open and friendly. Coming here, you\'ll find people from all around the country, with different backgrounds, different cultures and even languages too. Don\'t make the mistake of maintaining a friend circle consisting of only people with similar interests, or from the same community as you. 2. Explore yourself This is the time to explore your interests. My advice would be to try out all things and everything. Attend the initial sessions of all the clubs, try out all the sports. Believe me, you might find something that you\'ve never even considered, to be extremely fun or something you\'re naturally good at. Try out some debating, dancing, jamming some music, as I said everything really. 3. Cause CG will not make you smile, but memories will. Don\'t focus solely on academics but at the same time, don\'t ignore them completely. Remember, this is the time to do some crazy fun stuff, make some long lasting memories. You\'ll be burdened by responsibilities after you graduate, so this is really the best time to just enjoy yourself. But then again, an easy mistake that you can make is to ignore the academics completely. Simply put, maintain a good balance.',
    author: 'Anonymous',
    date: 'Aug 10, 2019',
    readMinutes: 2,
    tag: BlogTag.academic,
  ),
  BlogPost(
    id: '14',
    title: 'Interesting Places to visit near Ropar',
    summary: 'A short appreciation for the canal near IIT Ropar, a perfect spot for peace, introspection, and enjoying a beautiful sunset with friends.',
    content:
        'I don’t know if people would consider it a place worth visiting or not but for me its surely a bliss and I would surely recommend everyone to visit the beautiful place once. No matter, if it’s the happy time after the exams or the times of sadness when I wished for solace, canal is always an extremely close option for me each and every time. The tranquility and peace it have to offer is immense and those deep moments of self introspection are great. Enjoying the sunset at the canal with friends and music and some nice food packagings are sufficient to complete my day on a happy note. On the whole, just a bus to tc and 5-10 minutes walk is enough for any mood for me.',
    author: 'Aneeket Mangal',
    date: 'Jun 26, 2020',
    readMinutes: 2,
    tag: BlogTag.campus,
  ),
  BlogPost(
    id: '15',
    title: 'ADVITIYA-Technical Fest of IIT Ropar',
    summary: 'A glimpse into Advitya, IIT Ropar\'s annual 3-day technical fest filled with robotics, coding, workshops, and exciting star nights.',
    content:
        'Advitya , our annual technical fest is a 3 day journey of excitement and allure where you can explore your passion and potential in technology . It doesn\'t matter if you\'re a novice who\'s only looking for a glimpse into something new or an expert who\'s looking for an opportunity to leave their mark , Advitya has a place for everyone! Here\'s a peek into what you\'re in for: PHOTO GALLERY Be it robotics, aeromodelling, automatives or coding, with your days filled with events such as robo wars, derby racing, drone racing, exciting astro quizzes, workshops and talks, which are strategically aligned with the present day needs, and nights filled with DJ along with a distinguished Star Night, Advitya promises to be a getaway worth your time.',
    author: 'Anonymous',
    date: 'Feb 5, 2020',
    readMinutes: 1,
    tag: BlogTag.tech,
